    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can wrap it in another class which knows the type of your generic type.</p>\n\n<p>Eg,</p>\n\n<pre><code>class Wrapper {\n private Data&lt;Something&gt; data;\n}\nmapper.readValue(jsonString, Wrapper.class);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Here Something is a concrete type. You need a wrapper per reified type. Otherwise Jackson does not know what objects to create.</p>\n"
