    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can't do that: you must specify fully resolved type, like <code>Data&lt;MyType&gt;</code>. <code>T</code> is just a variable, and as is meaningless.</p>\n\n<p>But if you mean that <code>T</code> will be known, just not statically, you need to create equivalent of <code>TypeReference</code> dynamically. Other questions referenced may already mention this, but it should look something like:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public Data&lt;T&gt; read(InputStream json, Class&lt;T&gt; contentClass) {\n   JavaType type = mapper.getTypeFactory().constructParametricType(Data.class, contentClass);\n   return mapper.readValue(json, type);\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
